FBIS3-2271 "drchi045_e_94002" FBIS-CHI-94-045 Document Type:Daily Report 8 Mar 1994 Southeast Asia & Pacific PRC Reports Phnom Penh Attack on Pailin 4 Mar BK0603151494 Beijing China Radio International in Cambodian 1030 GMT 6 Mar 94 BK0603151494 Beijing China Radio International Language: Cambodian Article Type:BFN [Text] Ek Sereivoat, state secretary for national defense, disclosed on 5 March that the Khmer Royal Armed Forces began an offensive on 4 March against Pailin, the biggest stronghold of the Party of Democratic Kampuchea [PDK]. He said the attack was launched from areas south and north of Pailin city, but he did not reveal the scale of the attack or the number of the troops involved. It was reported on 4 March that the PDK's main forces had already been withdrawn from Pailin.
